                    <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/1284</idno>
                    <idno type="FIEY">209</idno>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" resp="http://syriaca.org" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/q http://syriaca.org/saints">Īšōʿsawrān was a
                        Zoroastrian Convert and later martyr from <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/13">Erbil</placeName>, whose life was
                        written by Īšōʿyaw III of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/993">Adiabene</placeName>. His life speaks a great deal of the interactions
                        between the Church of the East and Syrian Orthodox Church in the seventh
                        century.</note>
